# EMCAP Core Standards

1. Business code lives in `modules/` — never modify `platform/` core for a business feature.
2. Enable features via `config/platform.yaml`, not hard-coded flags.
3. Follow layered architecture: Presentation → Application (CQRS) → Platform Services → Infrastructure.
4. Map changes to SDD requirement IDs in `spec/sdd/03-traceability-matrix.md`.
5. New optional subsystems must default to disabled unless SDD specifies otherwise.
6. Before coding: read `docs/dev/codebase-index.md` and `docs/dev/known-pitfalls.md`.
7. Follow recipes in `docs/dev/recipes/`; update docs in the **same change** — `docs/dev/recipes/sync-docs-after-change.md` (`.cursor/rules/emcap-doc-sync.mdc`).
8. Reusable web UI lives in `clients/web/src/app/shared/`; pages compose shared components.
